body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, my name is Patrick Martin from Secure Auto Services. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Laura. For security purposes, could you provide the first four digits of your phone number and the last two digits of your social security number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, the first four digits of my phone number are seven seven seven two, and the last two digits of my social security number are eight nine.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Laura. Can you also confirm the model of your car and the year of manufacture?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, I drive a blue Toyota Corolla and it's a two zero one eight model.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Laura. Your details have been noted. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all for now. Thank you.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Laura. Feel free to reach out if you have any further queries. Have a great day.
